{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Darlington Pair Experiment",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Darlington Pair Experiment",
    "description": "Build a two-NPN Darlington pair on top of the lesson 58 switch. Q2 (east tile, 6,7) is wired like lesson 58: USB → T → 470Ω → LED → collector, emitter → ground. Add Q1 (7,7) beside it: route tact → 10kΩ → Q1 base (west), Q1 emitter (south) → Q2 base (west) with corners/straights, and tie both collectors to the LED branch. The pair needs much less base current than one transistor (lesson 58) for the same LED — gain is roughly β×β. Hand-route the Darlington link on your plate; magnet connectivity in this file is not finalized."
  },
